If the program needs to handle a 10GB CSV file, I would switch to background processing instead of a single request, use chunked uploads with resume support,
and process the data in batches to avoid memory issues. I’d also optimize duplicate checks by using bulk queries or a staging table, add indexes on key database
fields, and run multiple batches in parallel to speed up processing. This ensures the system remains fast, memory-efficient, and reliable with very large files.
